fields.name: CareConnectDetailsText
fields.fieldText:
Care Connect Details


Please fill in the below Care Connect specific fields:

fields.name: Type
fields.fieldText: Type
fields.helpText:
No Contact Took Place

Only use this code where the session is recorded as a no-show.


Assessment

Determination of a persons mental health status and need for mental health services, made by a suitably trained mental health professional. This involves:

  • Interview and observation
  • Evaluation of history and presenting problems
  • Consultation with the persons family (if applicable)
  • Formation of problems/issues
  • Documentation of a preliminary diagnosis
  • Creation of a treatment plan

Structured Psychological Intervention


Interventions involving structured interactions using recognized psychological methods, designed to alleviate psychological distress, change maladaptive behavior, and foster mental health. Examples include:

  • Psycho-education (including motivational interviewing)
  • Cognitive-behavioral therapies
  • Relaxation strategies
  • Skills training
  • Interpersonal therapy

These interventions can be delivered individually or in groups, typically in an office or community setting, by trained professionals or individuals with appropriate competencies.


Other Psychological Intervention


Psychological interventions that do not meet the criteria for structured psychological intervention.


Clinical Care Coordination/Liaison


Activities focused on working in partnership with other health care and service providers to coordinate and integrate service delivery, aiming to improve clinical outcomes. This includes:

  • Consultation and liaison with primary health care providers, emergency services, rehabilitation, support services, family, friends, and other support networks.

Clinical Nursing Services


Services delivered by mental health nurses aimed at providing clinical support, including:

  • Monitoring mental state
  • Liaising with family and carers
  • Administering and monitoring medication compliance
  • Providing physical health care information and assistance
  • Improving links to other health professionals

Child or Youth-Specific Assistance NEC


Services for children or young people that cannot be described elsewhere. Examples include:

  • Advising a childs teacher on educational support
  • Assisting a young person in their work environment

Note: Use this code only for services that cannot be described by any other Service Type.


Suicide Prevention Specific Assistance NEC


Services for clients at risk of suicide that cannot be described elsewhere. Examples include:

  • Advising on workplace changes
  • Assisting a young person in school
  • Supporting community-based group participation

Note: Use this code only for services that cannot be described by any other Service Type.


Cultural Specific Assistance NEC


Culturally appropriate services for Aboriginal or Torres Strait Islander clients that cannot be described elsewhere. Examples include:

  • Working with the clients community support network, such as family, carers, traditional healers, and social and emotional wellbeing counsellors.

Note: Use this code only for services that cannot be described by any other Service Type.


Psychosocial Support


Services focusing on building capacity and stability in areas such as:

  • Social skills and friendships
  • Family connections
  • Managing daily living needs
  • Financial management and budgeting
  • Finding and maintaining a home
  • Vocational skills and goals
  • Educational and training goals
  • Maintaining physical wellbeing
  • Building broader life skills (confidence, resilience)

These services are usually delivered by non-clinical providers, including peer support workers with lived experience of mental illness. They can be delivered in all episodes of care but are mainly associated with episodes where the Principal Focus of Treatment Plan is classified as Psychosocial Support.

fields.name: Participants
fields.fieldText: Participants
fields.helpText:
Individual

Sessions delivered individually to a single client without third-party participants.


Client Group

Sessions delivered on a group basis to two or more clients.


Family / Client Support Network

Sessions delivered to the family or social support persons of the client, with or without the participation of the client.


Other Health Professional or Service Provider

Sessions involve another health professional or service provider (in addition to the Practitioner/s), without the participation of the client or family support network.


Other

Sessions delivered to other third parties (e.g., teachers, employers), with or without the participation of the client.

fields.name: Client_Participation_Indicator
fields.fieldText: Client Participation Indicator
fields.helpText:
Sessions are not restricted to in-person communication but can include telephone, video link, or other forms of direct communication.


Yes

Sessions between a mental health service provider and the patient/client, where the patient/client is participating and the contact would normally warrant a dated entry in their clinical record.


No

Sessions between a mental health service provider and third party(ies) where the patient/client is not participating, though the contact would normally warrant a dated entry in the patient's/client's clinical record.


Note: Where a client intended to participate in a service contact but failed to attend, the Client Participation Indicator should be recorded as Yes and No Show should be recorded as Yes

fields.name: No_Show
fields.fieldText: No Show
fields.helpText:
Yes

The intended participant(s) failed to attend the appointment.


No

The intended participant(s) attended the appointment.
